snippet.title: Arcade Game: Millipede (1982 Atari)
snippet.description:
A gallary shooting 'em up game sequel to the all-time classic 1980 arcade game but not as successful that Atari had hoped for. With DDT bombs that destroys mushrooms, flowers, and enemies if the archer hits it. It includes, spiders, inchworms, mosquitoes, dragonflies, ants, earwigs, beetles, and more.

For the arcade original version of the first centipede game in 1980. watch here:
https://youtu.be/j8CZdoPAgMU


Note: Used Invincibility Cheat. The Game is endless. After seeing the levels start repeating, I killed myself afterwards.
